154.1	Madeleine_Albright	Madeleine Albright	Madeleine Korbelová Albright (born May 15, 1937) is the first woman to become a United States Secretary of State. She was appointed by U.S. President Bill Clinton on December 5, 1996, and was unanimously confirmed by a U.S. Senate vote of 99–0. She was sworn in on January 23, 1997.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b2/Secretary_of_State_Madeleine_Albright.jpg/250px-Secretary_of_State_Madeleine_Albright.jpg
